bit_field.name: RDP
bit_field.description: RAM Depth Register. Defines the depth, in words, of the trace RAM. This value is configurable in the RTL, but fixed at synthesis. Supported depth in powers of 2 only. Reset value = Ram Depth that is given by a Verilog tick define.

bit_field.name: Full
bit_field.description: RAM Full. The flag indicates when the RAM write pointer has wrapped around.

bit_field.name: Triggered
bit_field.description: The Triggered bit is set when a trigger has been observed. This does not indicate that a trigger has been embedded in the trace data by the formatter, but is determined by the programming of the Formatter and Flush Control Register.

bit_field.name: AcqComp
bit_field.description: Acquisition complete.

bit_field.name: FtEmpty
bit_field.description: Formatter pipeline empty. All data stored to RAM.

bit_field.name: RRD
bit_field.description: RAM Read Data. Data read from the ETB Trace RAM.

bit_field.name: RRP
bit_field.description: RAM Read Pointer. Sets the read pointer used to read entries from the Trace RAM over the APB interface.

bit_field.name: RWP
bit_field.description: RAM Write Pointer. Sets the write pointer used to write entries from the CoreSight bus into the Trace RAM.

bit_field.name: TRG
bit_field.description: Trigger Counter Register.

bit_field.name: TraceCaptEn
bit_field.description: ETB Trace Capture Enable.

bit_field.name: RWD
bit_field.description: Data written to the ETB Trace RAM.

bit_field.name: FlInProg
bit_field.description: Flush In Progress. This is an indication of the current state of AFVALIDS.

bit_field.name: FtStopped
bit_field.description: Formatter stopped. The formatter has received a stop request signal and all trace data and post-amble has been output. Any more trace data on the ATB interface is ignored and ATREADYS goes HIGH.

bit_field.name: EnFTC
bit_field.description: Enable Formatting. Do not embed Triggers into the formatted stream. Trace disable cycles and triggers are indicated by TRACECTL, where fitted. Can only be changed when FtStopped is HIGH. This bit is clear on reset.

bit_field.name: EnFCont
bit_field.description: Continuous Formatting. Continuous mode in the ETB corresponds to normal mode with the embedding of triggers. Can only be changed when FtStopped is HIGH. This bit is clear on reset.

bit_field.name: FOnFlIn
bit_field.description: Generate flush using the FLUSHIN interface. Set this bit to enable use of the FLUSHIN connection. This bit is clear on reset.

bit_field.name: FOnTrig
bit_field.description: Generate flush using Trigger event. Set this bit to cause a flush of data in the system when a Trigger Event occurs. This bit is clear on reset.

bit_field.name: FOnMan
bit_field.description: Manually generate a flush of the system. Setting this bit causes a flush to be generated. This is cleared when this flush has been serviced. This bit is clear on reset.

bit_field.name: TrigIn
bit_field.description: Indicate a trigger on TRIGIN being asserted

bit_field.name: TrigEvt
bit_field.description: Indicate a trigger on a Trigger Event.

bit_field.name: TrigFl
bit_field.description: Indicate a trigger on Flush completion (AFREADYS being returned).

bit_field.name: StopFl
bit_field.description: Stop the formatter when a flush has completed (return of AFREADYS). This forces the FIFO to drain off any part-completed packets. Setting this bit enables this function but this is clear on reset (disabled).

bit_field.name: StopTrig
bit_field.description: Stop the formatter when a Trigger Event has been observed. Reset to disabled (zero).

bit_field.name: ACQCOMP
bit_field.description: Set the value of ACQCOMP

bit_field.name: FULL
bit_field.description: Set the value of FULL

bit_field.name: TRIGINACK
bit_field.description: Set the value of TRIGINACK

bit_field.name: FLUSHINACK
bit_field.description: Set the value of FLUSHINACK

bit_field.name: TRIGIN
bit_field.description: Read the value of TRIGIN

bit_field.name: FLUSHIN
bit_field.description: Read the value of FLUSHIN

bit_field.name: ATDATA0
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATDATAS[0]

bit_field.name: ATDATA7
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATDATAS[7]

bit_field.name: ATDATA15
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATDATAS[15]

bit_field.name: ATDATA23
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATDATAS[23]

bit_field.name: ATDATA31
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATDATAS[31]

bit_field.name: ATREADYS
bit_field.description: Set the value of ATREADYS

bit_field.name: AFVALIDS
bit_field.description: Set the value of AFVALIDS

bit_field.name: ATID
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATIDS

bit_field.name: ATVALID
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATVALIDS

bit_field.name: AFREADY
bit_field.description: Read the value of AFREADYS

bit_field.name: ATBYTES
bit_field.description: Read the value of ATBYTESS

bit_field.name: IntegrationMode
bit_field.description: Integration mode. When set, the component enters integration mode, enabling topology detection or integration testing to be performed. At reset the component must enter functional mode. If no integration functionality is implemented, this bit must read as zero.

bit_field.name: CLAIMSET
bit_field.description: A bit programmable register bank which sets the Claim Tag Value.

bit_field.name: CLAIMCLR
bit_field.description: A bit programmable register bank that is zero at reset.

bit_field.name: WriteAccessCode
bit_field.description: Write Access Code. A write of 0xC5ACCE55 enables further write access to this device. An invalid write will have the affect of removing write access.

bit_field.name: IMP
bit_field.description: Lock mechanism is implemented. When PADDRDBG31 is HIGH, the Lock Status Register reads as 0x0 indicating that no lock exists. When PADDRDBG31 is LOW, the Lock Status Register reads as 0x3 from reset. This indicates a 32-bit lock access mechanism is present and is locked

bit_field.name: STATUS
bit_field.description: Lock Status. This bit is HIGH when the device is locked, and LOW when unlocked.

bit_field_value.name: LSR_STATUS_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Write access to the component is blocked. All writes to control registers are ignored. Reads are permitted.

bit_field.name: s8BIT
bit_field.description: Access Lock Register size. This bit reads 0 to indicate 32-bit register is present.

bit_field.name: AuthenticationStatus
bit_field.description: Authentication Status. Reports the required security level. This is set to 0x00 for functionality not implemented.

bit_field.name: HLIM
bit_field.description: Hidden Level of Input Multiplexing. When non-zero this value indicates the type/number of ATB multiplexing present on the input to the ATB. Currently only 0x00 is supported (no multiplexing present). This value is used to assist topology detection of the ATB structure.

bit_field.name: Sync
bit_field.description: Indicates that the ETB RAM operates synchronously to ATCLK.

bit_field.name: DevTypeID
bit_field.description: Device Type Identifier 0x21 indicates this device is a trace sink and specifically an ETB.

bit_field.name: JEP106
bit_field.description: JEP106 continuation code.

bit_field.name: c4KB
bit_field.description: 4KB Count

bit_field.name: PartNumber
bit_field.description: Part Number [7:0]

bit_field.name: PartNumber
bit_field.description: Part Number [11:8]

bit_field.name: JEP106_identity_code
bit_field.description: JEP106 identity code [3:0]

bit_field.name: JEP106_identity_code
bit_field.description: JEP106 identity code [6:4]

bit_field.name: CustomerModified
bit_field.description: Customer Modified.

bit_field.description: Component class

bit_field_value.description: PrimeCell of system component with no standardized register layout, for backward compatibility.
